---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const headHtml = "<title>NotEnoughCoins FAQ | Current Hypixel SkyBlock Tool Answers</title>\n        <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Common questions and direct answers about NotEnoughCoins, the migration offer that expired in January 2026, and where to go now for flip finders, AH scanners, bazaar prices, craft tools, historical sale context and alerts.\">\n        <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/faq\">\n\n        <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n            {\n                \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n                \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\n                \"mainEntity\": [\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Is NotEnoughCoins still an active project?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"The paid NotEnoughCoins mod is discontinued, but the website is still active as a Hypixel SkyBlock guide, FAQ and tool hub.\"\n                        }\n                    },\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Did the NEC to SkyCofl migration offer expire?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"Yes. The free one-year claim window expired in January 2026, and the legacy claim flow is preserved only as historical context.\"\n                        }\n                    },\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Where should I go for current Hypixel SkyBlock flipping data?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"Start with SkyCofl's AH flipper, flips hub and premium bazaar. For ranked-board interfaces compare Skyblock.bz flips, BazaarPro and BazaarTracker smart flips.\"\n                        }\n                    },\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Where can I find a Hypixel SkyBlock AH scanner or flip finder?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"Start with the free SkyCofl flipper, then compare BazaarPro auction flips, Skyblock.bz flips and BazaarTracker auctions when you want tighter filters or ranked discovery.\"\n                        }\n                    },\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Where can I check bazaar prices, profitable crafts, historical sale context or alerts?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"Use SkyCofl bazaar, crafts, recent flips, low supply and notifier subscriptions, plus BazaarTracker margin, demand and crafts, BazaarPro market trends and craft & forge flips, and Skyblock.bz manipulation and crash views.\"\n                        }\n                    },\n                    {\n                        \"@type\": \"Question\",\n                        \"name\": \"Where can I compare the different flipping tools?\",\n                        \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n                            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n                            \"text\": \"Use the dedicated flipping tools comparison page on NotEnoughCoins. It compares SkyCofl, Skyblock.bz, BazaarPro, BazaarTracker, Donut and ANE by public features rather than hype.\"\n                        }\n                    }\n                ]\n            }\n        </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n            <div class=\"site-shell\">\n                <section class=\"hero\">\n                    <span class=\"badge\">FAQ</span>\n                    <h1>Questions about NotEnoughCoins and current Hypixel SkyBlock tools</h1>\n                    <p class=\"lede\">This page gives direct, current answers about the shutdown, where the live tooling moved, and which tool surface answers each common SkyBlock question.</p>\n                </section>\n\n                <section class=\"section faq-list\">\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\" open>\n                        <summary>Is NotEnoughCoins still an active project?</summary>\n                        <p>The paid NotEnoughCoins mod is discontinued, but the NotEnoughCoins site is still here as a Hypixel SkyBlock guide and tool hub. It now points readers at the maintained SkyBlock tool stack and the current SkyCofl workflow. The quickest overview is the <a href=\"/guides/flipping-tools-comparison-2026\">flipping tools comparison guide</a>.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Did the NEC to SkyCofl migration offer expire?</summary>\n                        <p>Yes. The free one-year claim window expired in January 2026. The legacy command flow is preserved here only as historical context and should not be treated as an active entitlement path.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Where should I go for current Hypixel SkyBlock flipping data?</summary>\n                        <p>For live auction and bazaar data, start with the free, modifier-aware <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl AH flipper</a> and <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/premiumBazaar\">premium bazaar</a>. If you want the broader map of alternative interfaces after that, use the <a href=\"/guides/flipping-tools-comparison-2026\">comparison guide</a>.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Where can I find a Hypixel SkyBlock AH scanner or flip finder?</summary>\n                        <p>If you mean a real-time auction scanner or flip finder, start with the free <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl flipper</a>. The <a href=\"/guides/flipping-tools-comparison-2026\">comparison guide</a> covers the alternative ranked and paid workflows.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Where can I check bazaar prices, profitable crafts, historical sale context or alerts?</summary>\n                        <p>For live bazaar prices and craft checks, use <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a> and <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/crafts\">SkyCofl crafts</a>. For sale context and thin-market warnings, use <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/recentFlips\">recent flips</a> and <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">low supply</a>. The <a href=\"/guides/flipping-tools-comparison-2026\">comparison guide</a> maps the broader tool stack when you want more than one workflow.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Why keep this domain online if NEC is closed?</summary>\n                        <p>It still helps former NEC users and current SkyBlock players in two ways: it gives a clear note that the paid mod was discontinued, and it keeps a set of evergreen guide pages about flipping, slayers, mining and farming that route readers toward maintained dashboards.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Was NEC historically considered safe?</summary>\n                        <p>The historical NEC positioning was that it was not a RAT and that its premium code was viewable by users. This guide series does not distribute the old premium service; it only preserves the public historical context and points readers to the maintained SkyCofl stack.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Is there still a mod download associated with this site?</summary>\n                        <p>Not for NEC as a live product. If you want maintained Coflnet tooling, use the current <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/mod\">SkyCofl mod page</a> instead of looking for legacy NEC downloads.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Why are there articles here now?</summary>\n                        <p>The site now publishes long-form Hypixel SkyBlock money-making guides that are grounded in creator walkthrough transcripts and then supported with outbound links to live data tools. That keeps the guide series useful without pretending NEC is still operating.</p>\n                    </details>\n\n                    <details class=\"faq-card\">\n                        <summary>Where can I compare the different flipping tools?</summary>\n                        <p>The dedicated <a href=\"/guides/flipping-tools-comparison-2026\">flipping tools comparison</a> contrasts SkyCofl, Skyblock.bz, BazaarPro, BazaarTracker, Donut and ANE on visible public features (real-time data, modifier-aware filters, manipulation detection, notifier alerts, craft &amp; forge coverage) instead of affiliate-style hype. The home-page tool cards link straight to each feature surface.</p>\n                    </details>\n                </section>\n            </div>\n        </main>";
---

<Base headHtml={headHtml} bodyHtml={bodyHtml} />
